pokedexEntries.gold: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure for its beauty.
pokedexEntries.silver: In a south sea nation, the people live in communities that are built on groups of these Pokémon.
pokedexEntries.crystal: The points on its head absorb nutrients from clear water. They cannot survive in polluted water.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Corsola's branches glitter very beautifully in seven colors when they catch sunlight. If any branch breaks off, this Pokémon grows it back in just one night.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Clusters of Corsola congregate in warm seas where they serve as ideal hiding places for smaller Pokémon. When the water temperature falls, this Pokémon migrates to the southern seas.
pokedexEntries.emerald: Corsola live in warm southern seas. If the sea becomes polluted, the beautiful coral stalks become discolored and crumble away in tatters.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: In a south sea nation, the people live in communities that are built on groups of these Pokémon.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure for its beauty.
pokedexEntries.diamond: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can't live in polluted waters.

pokedexEntries.black2: They prefer unpolluted southern seas. Their coral branches lose their color and deteriorate in dirty water.
pokedexEntries.white2: They prefer unpolluted southern seas. Their coral branches lose their color and deteriorate in dirty water.

pokedexEntries.y: They prefer unpolluted southern seas. Their coral branches lose their color and deteriorate in dirty water.
pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Corsola's branches glitter very beautifully in seven colors when they catch sunlight. If any branch breaks off, this Pokémon grows it back in just one night.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: Clusters of Corsola congregate in warm seas where they serve as ideal hiding places for smaller Pokémon. When the water temperature falls, this Pokémon migrates to the southern seas.
pokedexEntries.sun: Coral branches grow from its head. They break off quite easily, but they grow back in about three days.
pokedexEntries.moon: Pursued by Mareanie for the branches on its head, this Pokémon will sometimes snap its own branches off as a diversion while it escapes.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: The pink of Corsola that live in Alola is deep and vibrant, thanks to seas filled with nutrition.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: In Alola, where their natural enemies Mareanie are plentiful, many Corsola have stubby branches on their heads.
